deck_excerpt: want a deck similar to empty jar, but more about building and destroying fields and hands...? then look no further than my Destroy Build Destroy deck;
deck_description: The idea behind the deck is to use an unconventional and annoying to stop chain of endless flip summoning to absolutely wreck every kind of field that does not have an immediate answer when the time comes.  The set up is quite simple All-Out Attack and Morphing jar 2... thats it any other critter you have on the field is a bonus. MJ2 Special summons a mon from your deck; A-OA forces every special summoned mon to flip into atk mode and declare an attack if possible. So long as you can keep hitting an MJ2 as one of your summons the loop continues indefinely and since everything that cannot be summoned is sent to the GY. it only takes a few hits of Morphing Jar (1) to destroy the rest of an opponents deck already near exausted from there use of cards like Desire and all their searching.  Destroy the field build the field then destroy it once more; thats what this deck is about at its core.

deck_excerpt: This deck is meant to set up a field of Light fairies and use effect damage to crush opponents in a few turns. More friends on the field the greater t
deck_description: Anzu=Tae was all about friendship; she herself was not much of a player so her decks were questionable at best. I am trying to correct this by showing a deck centered around swarming being enough even if the brute force is lacking.  Athena is the heart of the deck and its not easily gained; but once Big Sis Athena is on the field directing her Sisters in arms it all comes together. Athena's effect is that each summon of a fairy type causes 600 dam; once per turn she can tribute another fairy to summon a fairy from the GY. Fairy Archer is the best friend of Athena and she only shines when Athena is surrounded by many friends. Fairy archer is the other corner stone as she can inact some of the larger effect damage pushes in this deck. For each light fairy I think its 300 dam; she launches her Solar Ray some times but its only good for 600 per itself.  Once when using it against another of my decks I wanted to see how much effect damage was possible... well 6 light fairy times 900+ 2 or 3 summons for 600 each= 7200 damage and thats 1 Solar ray with all copies going its another 7200 more so unlikely as it is to pull off 10K+ effect damage is possible in one round; how much can you pull off?

deck_excerpt: This is an archive Deck for the 2002 video game Eternal Duelist Soul. It is not intended for modern day play.
deck_description: This Deck is built to archive the old 2002 video game Eternal Duelist Soul. Deck #1 by SlimSleezy Black Luster Soldier deck revolves around trying to stall until you can pull out your Black Luster Soldier through deck-searching. You do this primarily by using beat down 4 stars, or high defense stall monsters. In this case, this version of the deck is all traditional attack based monsters. However, you can get creative and add in high attack but improbable monsters that won't likely attack on their own, like Jirai Gumo (2200ATK), Dark Elf(2000ATK), and Panther Warrior(2000ATK). Keep your high attack monsters on the field while working towards your win condition. You don't necessarily have to attack, in fact, while stalling it may be in your favor to reconsider playing too offensive without your trump card ready. You can experiment with having defense cards in your deck as well. However, the difference between having 2000 defense or 1900 attack is so little that it's worth being able to steadily beat down the enemy while you wait. You look for your Black Luster Ritual with Sonic Bird, and you look for Black Luster Soldier with Senju Of The Thousand Hands. You then combine them with sacrificing two of your beat down stall monsters and ritual summon Black Luster Soldier It's a very primitive playstyle even for 2002,but it's actually quite fun. It's fast, and snappy, and within it's own meta it is very hard to keep up with. It has very limited card swap potential, most of the cards are mandatory for it work correctly.

deck_excerpt: Dark Magician but with Ultimate Falcon as an optional boss monster.
deck_description: Basically an ultimate falcon turbo but with a chance of winning. Depending on what you open, you will either be doing normal dark magician plays or going into Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon. Your combo will start by trying to get 2 level 7 monsters on the board. This can be done with Dark Magic Veil bringing out a level 7 from the GY, with Magician's Souls special summoning a Dark Magician from the GY, or with Advanced Ritual Art summoning Magician of Chaos. Once you have accomplished that, you can go into Raidraptor - Arsenal Falcon. Using Arsenal Falcon, you can special summon Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius. Use Tribute Lanius to send Raider's Wing to the GY. Detach one material from Arsenal Falcon and special summon Raider's Wing from the GY, then link summon Raidraptor - Wise Strix using Arsenal Falcon and Tribute Lanius. Special summon another copy of either Tribute Lanius or Raider's Wing from your deck and Xyz into Raidraptor - Force Strix. Using Force Strix's effect will allow you to add Raidraptor -  Singing Lanius to your hand and set Phantom Knight's Rank-Up-Magic Force to your field. You can now sepical summon Singing Lanius and link away Wise Strix. Once you are done, use the Rank-Up-Magic to special summon Ultimate Falcon using Force Strix. Optimally, your end board is now Crusadia Astram + Ultimate Falcon with Dark Magician distruption during your opponents turn.  If you did not open a way to get 2 Level 7 monsters on the field, or you know your opponent can easily disrupt your path to ultimate falcon, you still have the Dark Magician path open. With Magician of Chaos' quick effect destruction and circle banish, you will find it easy to disrupt your opponent on their turn. Do note however, that this deck will not survive the grind game, as you will run out of resources quickly.  Have fun with this meme deck I made. Any feedback is welcome.

deck_description: Kodachi is what you might call a muscle brained and honest fool. She believes in one truth and one person and nothing else.  Yume is the person; and the truth is Atk is the only form of def that exists in a fight. So her decks contain weapons and those that wield them and going second is her only choice. Turn without a battle phase is a waste of time.  This deck is the version she starts with in my story. Harpy Girl and Souls of the forgotten are some of my signature cards with my characters if they have a purpose at all. Amulet of Ambitions turns my Lv 2 normys into dangerous threats against high level synchros or main deck monsters.  Benny is her ultimate atker as he gets one per equip on him his norm and a "second" with Twin swords meaning he can overcome a lot. one megamorph on a chainsaw is enough to overcome most threats.  remember with this deck attacking really is your only chance at preventing future threats so never hesitate.

deck_name: My Evil Eye & Evil twin/ Live twin Post LIOV- July 2021
deck_excerpt: Evil eye + Evil Twin= Alright! I can see that I will have to teach you how to be  villans
deck_description: What do we need? YES!!! More evil!!   Good day ladies and gentlemen, today another remaster of another crazy inspiration I had months ago, but now totally (or almost) competitive . I present to you My Evil eye & Evil★Twin deck!!   How did this come to be?   Think about, the main aggressive core of each archetype is fiend, Evil★Twin monster locks you on fiend type  from extra deck… was natural (at least for me) to use these two archetypes together like best friends, to become  the most evil deck of my house!!   What is the point of playing this deck?   If you like the gameplay of the Evil★Twin(summon one of lil-la or ki-sikil to summon one different of the one that you summon and go in the control aspect of this archetype) will love this deck, because Evil eye  is an extreme versatil and control deck as well . Serziel can seach   eye of selene and from there... mate... your opponent will be lucky if he’d have a chance to play . Now you can imagine how  these two engines would work together... Am I right?!!   Downsides??   This deck is to normal summon reliant, because  Serzie for some reason can only search Eye of selene if she  was normal summon , and guess what? The  Live☆Twin  can only active their effect if you control no monster on the field, becmo a little incosist . To mitigate this effect, Secret password and  Live☆Twin Home will be yours bests friends . Why? Let’s found about!!   Starter:   3XSecret Password;   3xLive☆Twin Home;  1xTerraforming; 3xEvil Eye Domain - Pareidolia: if for any reason your first hand  be at least on of this card, you will have a good live playing in this game . Secret password can search your Live☆Twin Home from then you will be able to summon  any Live☆Twin  monster  without wasting your normal summon . From there if you have  terraforming  you can  bring Evil Eye Domain - Pareidolia, to finally use your normal summon and summon  Serziel, Watcher of the Evil Eye,  to continue your play .  Evil Eye Domain - Pareidolia  can also recover any of your Evil eye monsters from you GY if were pop up by effect( even yours effects) . The perfect hand would be at least one Secret password  and a terraforming .   3 Live☆Twin Lil-la:  you can normal summon her and go in typical evil twin play with need . I recommend  bringing  Live☆Twin Ki-sikil Frost  with her toeffect, from then  draw a card with your opponent  try anything naughty .   3 Live☆Twin Ki-sikil: The same as Lil-la , you can bring Live☆Twin Lil-la Treat  for later on .   3 Serziel, Watcher of the Evil Eye: Her effect while equipped with Eye of selene is… outrageous, use as a machine gun!    Extenders!   2 Live☆Twin Ki-sikil Frost 1 Live☆Twin Lil-la Treat:   both can be summoned easily by their own effect (if you control the other live twin for exemple .   2 Evil Eye Awakening:   if you are low  in resource,  Evil Eye Awakening  to revive any of your evil eye monsters or  if  you have Eye of selene on the field, you could even summon  Serziel or Medusa, Watcher of the Evil Eye  to your field from  your deck .  Neat, isn’t it?   1 Medusa, Watcher of the Evil Eye:  to recover any evil eye’s spell from your grave .   2 Evil Eye Reemergence:  this card can easily put a token (or 2 depending on Eye of selene) , on the field, helping even more the Evil★Twin  link play , for example . It also provides a decent protection for your Evil eyes spell cards .     1 Monster Reborn: Free summon from my Gy . You can even steal a dragoon!! Cheers! (Remember to  give back his/her card , you thief!)   1 Knightmare Gryphon: Evil★Twin best friend . A fiend type monster that can recycle any spell card from you Gy if it’s co-linked with something . what is something? Yes , you Evil★Twin monster!!   Hand traps lineup!!    2 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring; 2 Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion:  my primary way to defend myself . Ash is literally our Maxx “c ”, a real staple ( even I don't like her and her massive forehead), and Belle is my little baby who protects me from anything from my opponent GY .   2 Evil Eye Retribution: A Solemn Judgment  of this archetype, this insane card can activate even from your hand if you have Eye of selene in the field.   3 Artifact Lancea; 3 D .D . Crow; 1 Red Reboot;1 Skull Meister: Very useful hand traps that I decided to put on the side . Lancea, dinosaur/tri-brigade killer, Crow, Benten demise . Red Reboot, A crime against humanity and golden lord; Meister, Belle older brother .   DEFENCES!!!    1 Knightmare Cerberus;1 Knightmare Phoenix;1 Knightmare Unicorn: the first one pops any monster, the second pops  one any spell/trap; the third one is the knightmare fuel for a certain Golden lord . Also they are the best friends of Evil★Twin .   3 Solemn Judgment: a big no, no, no .   1 Number 65: Djinn Buster:  a really interesting tech that I found that you can negate an effect monster( even hand traps), if you needed .   3 Dark Ruler No More ;1 Dinowrestler Pankratops; 3 Twin Twisters:  A anti dragoon/ dragon link  card, a free pop up; an anti mystic mine card respectively . All of that on my side   MY EYES!!!!   1 Evil Eye of Gorgoneio 2 Evil Eye of Selene: You own very eye on this deck .  Evil Eye of Gorgoneio boost an attack of a monster by the difference ( if lower) of your life points by of your opponent’s life points, and  Evil Eye of Selene boost an attack of a monster by 500 points every time that  activate a Evil eye spell card . A technique to confuse your opponent is to  put Evil Eye of Selene on the right and Evil Eye of Gorgoneio  on the left, cross-eyed  Evil eye .   Beater!!   1 Zerrziel, Ruler of the Evil Eyed: Can attack twice if you use a 2600 atk or more, and may… this man is scary! negates effects where he points to, pops cards … the only downside is that he is a link-3 .   2 Evil★Twin Ki-sikil;3 Evil★Twin Lil-la:  Sam and  Carly for our era,  pops and  can draw a card , the real stars for this deck .   2 Gorgon, Empress of the Evil Eyed: Negates effect monster   in a quick effect… hmm spicy!!   1 I:P Masquerena: one day . I will make a cosplay  about her . Can make your Unchained Abomination indestructible .   1 Unchained Abomination:  your main beater, this beast is a machine gun of pop, and has a high atk too and guess what? It’s a fiend!!   Conclusion   This deck is not near meta, not by a close , but it is a really fun and surprise deck to play on local  (when it returns), cause has a  high tier of interaction . The positive side of things is that you can be called by the name of the most evil duelist !! I hope  you like my silly guide, and I see you the next day .
